# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file
version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  SNYK-JS-BIGINTBUFFER-3364597:
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          Patched at the library level via patch-package (see
          patches/bigint-buffer+1.1.5.patch). No upstream fix exists for
          any version of bigint-buffer; maintainer has not responded.
          Our patch adds a null / non-Buffer type guard to toBigIntLE
          and toBigIntBE so the exact inputs that trigger the buffer
          overflow (CVE-2025-3194) throw TypeError instead of reaching
          the vulnerable native binding. The postinstall hook in
          package.json reapplies the patch on every install.
          Re-evaluate when a fixed upstream version ships or when
          @solana/spl-token drops its @solana/buffer-layout-utils
          dependency.
        created: 2026-04-23T00:00:00.000Z
        expires: 2027-04-23T00:00:00.000Z
